The director general of private security regulatory authority, Fazul Mohamed Ober has presided over a security heads meeting here in Nairobi. The meeting that brought together senior supervisors and managers of security firms has announced a number of reforms including those affecting security guards equipment and welfare. Top on the agenda was the issuance of firearms to guards manning key institutions and public spaces, mandatory training for security guards, vetting afresh of guards. Ober noted that he will issue a circular ment to initiate the roll out of the agreed reforms